  "texts": [
    "Epileptic power supply, a lack of knowledge or skills, problems with availability and accessibility, funding, inadequate professional development, disinclination to change, unreliable internet connections, and so on to name a few.",
    "Actors and stakeholders in the education sector like educators, policymakers, curriculum planners, and students can all work together to overcome these obstacles (Enang, 2022).",
    "AI algorithms and systems have been increasingly popular and well-known in recent times, particularly in the eld of education.",
    "At many educational installations, tablets have largely taken the role of books in the learning process and internet-based learning has become more common (Kairouz et al., 2021).",
    "Digital tools have transformed education and made learning more active and independent."
